    "1 3 thermore, Context-aware Pooling (Hayat et al. 2023c) achieves adaptive aggregation of relevant information in hypergraphs by introducing an attention mechanism that considers both local and global contextual information.",
    "This strategy not only enhances the model's understanding of the complex structure of hypergraphs, but also improves the relevance and effectiveness of information aggregation, which provides a strong support for research in the field of hypergraphs.",
    "When evaluating graph pooling methods, researchers often rely on several key collections of datasets, including TUDatasets (Morris et al. 2007), Benchmarking GNNs (Dwivedi et al. 2023), and the Open Graph Benchmark (OGB) (Hu et al. 2020).",
